==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aërification
<hw>A`⟦eum⟧r*i*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
F. <ets>a⟦eacute⟧rification</ets>. See <er>Aurify</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of combining air with another substance, or the
state of being filled with air.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of becoming a⟦eum⟧rified, or of changing
from a solid or liquid form into an a⟦eum⟧riform state; the state of
being a⟦eum⟧riform.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>A⟦eum⟧riform</ent>⟦br⟧
